x4freetext: Facility is not given.
During the angular distribution runs, angular
positions of three detectors were varied while a fourth
detector monitored the ground state proton group at a
fixed angle 165 degr.
Targets (15 keV in thickness) were fabricated by
evaporating calcium fluoride (CaF2) onto carbon foils
stabilized with a thin gold film.

COMMON in Sub 004-017 was changed,
REACTION code in Sub 004-017 was changed.
Elastically scattered alpha particles were measured
with +-0.5 degr. apertures at forward angles and +-1.5
degr. apertures at back angles with the aluminum foil
removed from the detectors.
